Description: Fix CVE-2026-49271: integer overflow in unci/icef compressed data handling
 The libheif uncompressed (unci) decoder validates icef compressed-unit
 offsets using an addition (unit_offset + unit_size) that can wrap due to
 uint64_t overflow. A crafted HEIF file can bypass the range check and
 cause the decoder to construct iterators outside the compressed item
 buffer, resulting in an out-of-bounds heap read and a crash
 (CWE-125, GHSA-r7qj-cg5r-r6vf).
 .
 This backport combines four upstream commits:
   * 5782bca (unci: prevent integer overflow when reading compressed data)
     ported to libheif/codecs/uncompressed/decoder_abstract.cc since the
     vulnerable iterator construction was relocated/renamed (formerly in
     libheif/codecs/uncompressed/unc_decoder.cc upstream).  In the 1.19.8
     target there was no prior bounds check at all, so the subtraction-form
     check is added new.
   * 0c44a74 (unci: prevent int overflow when reading icef ranges):
     replace 'implied_offset' with 'unitInfo.unit_offset' in the wrap
     check inside Box_icef::parse so the test reflects the actual offset
     used for the unit being parsed.
   * 596cf2c (add defensive check that DataExtent reads do not overflow):
     guard the cached-buffer DataExtent::read_data path against an
     offset+size wrap that would otherwise read out of bounds.
   * e9bf0c9 (unci: only compute implied_offset if used): only accumulate
     'implied_offset' when unit_offset_code == 0; accumulating it
     otherwise is unused and can itself overflow.
