+# Security False-Positive Analysis — CVE-2026-41071 (libheif, Debian trixie)
+
+**CVE-2026-41071** — *not-affected (false positive)*
+
+> Companion to CVE-2026-41069 / CVE-2026-32738 / CVE-2026-32739. Same HEIF
+> image-sequence `SampleAuxInfoReader` path; same `not-affected` verdict for
+> Debian trixie.
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|-------|
+| CVE | CVE-2026-41071 |
+| Package | `libheif` |
+| Distribution | Debian 13 (trixie) |
+| Shipped version | `1.19.8` (`1.19.8-1`) |
+| Verdict | **not-affected** — vulnerable code not present |
+| Reason class | Feature introduced in the next minor release (1.20.0), after the shipped version |
+| Upstream advisory | https://github.com/strukturag/libheif/security/advisories/GHSA-xj92-xjff-h8w3 |
+| Upstream fix | https://github.com/strukturag/libheif/commit/f20c81745e917b4c496615140385c86d7a2fa58d |
+
+---
+
+## 1. Summary
+
+CVE-2026-41071 is a heap-buffer over-read in `SampleAuxInfoReader` when a
+crafted HEIF sequence declares more `saiz` samples than the track's chunk
+table covers. The constructor walks `saiz->get_num_samples()` without
+bounding against `chunks.size()`.
+
+Debian trixie ships **libheif 1.19.8**. `SampleAuxInfoReader` and
+`libheif/sequences/` were introduced in **libheif 1.20.0** and are absent
+from 1.19.8.
+
+**Conclusion: CVE-2026-41071 is a false positive for trixie and should be marked
+`not-affected`.**
+
+---
+
+## 2. Recommended triage entry
+
+```
+[trixie] - libheif <not-affected> (Image-sequence SampleAuxInfoReader —
+introduced in 1.20.0; trixie ships 1.19.8 which predates the feature)
+```
+
+---
+
+*Verdict: CVE-2026-41071 is a **false positive for Debian trixie (libheif 1.19.8)** —
+the affected code was introduced in 1.20.0 and does not exist in the shipped
+version.*
